Sentencas: Polycrystalline scheelite type Sr1-xBaxWO4 (x = 0.1, 0.2 & 0.3) materials were synthesized by the solid state sintering method and studied with respect to phase stability and ionic conductivity under condition of technological relevance for SOFC applications.
Titulo: Scheelite type Sr1-xBaxWO4 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) for possible application in Solid Oxide Fuel Cell electrolytes

Sentencas: All compounds crystallized in the single phase of tetragonal scheelite structure with the space group of I4(1)/a.
Titulo: Scheelite type Sr1-xBaxWO4 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) for possible application in Solid Oxide Fuel Cell electrolytes

Sentencas: Room temperature X-ray diffraction and subsequent Rietveld analysis confirms its symmetry, space group and structural parameters.
Titulo: Scheelite type Sr1-xBaxWO4 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) for possible application in Solid Oxide Fuel Cell electrolytes

Sentencas: SEM illustrates the highly dense compounds.
Titulo: Scheelite type Sr1-xBaxWO4 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) for possible application in Solid Oxide Fuel Cell electrolytes

Sentencas: Significant mass change was observed to prove the proton uptake at higher temperature by TG-DSC.
Titulo: Scheelite type Sr1-xBaxWO4 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) for possible application in Solid Oxide Fuel Cell electrolytes

Sentencas: All compound shows lower conductivity compared to the traditional BCZY perovskite structured materials.
Titulo: Scheelite type Sr1-xBaxWO4 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) for possible application in Solid Oxide Fuel Cell electrolytes

Sentencas: SBW with x = 0.3 exhibit the highest ionic conductivity among all compounds under wet argon condition which is 1.9 x 10(-6)
Titulo: Scheelite type Sr1-xBaxWO4 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) for possible application in Solid Oxide Fuel Cell electrolytes

Sentencas: Since this scheelite type compounds show significant conductivity, the new series of SBW could serve in IT-SOFC as proton conducting electrolyte.
